<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 8:01PM MDT until June 28 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Phillips County in northeastern Montana...
* Until 900 PM MDT.
* At 801 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Zortman,
moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Zortman, Phillips, Landusky and Sun Prairie.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
